oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Northeast Corner of Claiborne and Robertson Streets, c. late 1930s
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of the northeast corner of Claiborne Street and Robertson Street. The area was designated as the site for the J.C. Napier Homes around 1939. Photographed by the Nashville Housing Authority. Forms part of the MDHA Photograph Collection. 1 photograph : b & w.
